O-API-B1
Orchestrator
Get API details — happy path
Functional
1. Call GET /api/config/{externalProviderDatasetName} with valid dataset (e.g. PREFERENCES_AFFLUENT). 2. Verify response JSON.
200 OK with correct JSON fields (endpoint, method, headers, retryPolicy).
Validate that API successfully retrieves the configuration for a valid dataset name.
QA
O-API-B2
Orchestrator
Dataset not found
Negative
Call endpoint with a dataset name that does not exist in DB.
404 Not Found or 200 with empty body and appropriate message.
Ensure the API gracefully handles missing dataset names without crashing.
QA
O-API-B3
Orchestrator
Missing path parameter
Negative
Call /api/config/ without specifying the dataset name.
400 Bad Request or 404 with message “dataset name required”.
Confirm API validates input and fails fast for missing parameters.
QA
O-API-B4
Orchestrator
Response schema validation
Contract
Call API and inspect structure of response JSON.
JSON contains expected fields with correct data types.
Ensure returned configuration matches the expected schema.
QA
O-API-B5
Orchestrator
Malformed JSON in DB
Negative
Manually insert malformed JSON into api_configuration_value_text column for a dataset, then call API.
422 or 500 error with descriptive message; service should not crash.
Verify system handles corrupted JSON data gracefully.
QA
O-API-B6
Orchestrator
Large configuration payload
Performance
Store large JSON config (many headers/fields) and call API.
200 OK within acceptable latency (<500ms).
Validate performance and stability with large payloads.

